# {{project-name}}

{{description}}

A ApexRouter WASM tool plugin. Built as a [WebAssembly Component](https://component-model.bytecodealliance.org/)
that exports the `apexrouter:host/tool` WIT interface.

## Toolchain

```bash
rustup target add wasm32-wasip1
cargo install cargo-component
```

## Build

```bash
cargo component build --release
# produces target/wasm32-wasip1/release/{{project-name}}.wasm
```

## Install

```bash
mkdir -p ~/.apexrouter/plugins/{{project-name}}
cp plugin.toml ~/.apexrouter/plugins/{{project-name}}/
cp target/wasm32-wasip1/release/{{project-name}}.wasm \
   ~/.apexrouter/plugins/{{project-name}}/
```

The engine scans `~/.apexrouter/plugins/` at startup and loads any directory
that contains a `plugin.toml` with `[runtime] kind = "wasm"`.

## Signing (production)

Unsigned plugins load only when the engine is started with `--allow-unsigned`.
For production:

```bash
# Generate sig (ed25519 over component bytes)
apexrouter plugin sign --key ~/.apexrouter/signing-key ~/.apexrouter/plugins/{{project-name}}/
```

Authorize the matching public key for the engine by copying its `.pub`
file into `~/.apexrouter/trusted-keys/`.

## Test

```bash
cargo test
```

## Editing the plugin

The hello-world body lives in `src/lib.rs::Plugin::execute`. Update the
input schema in `Plugin::schema()` to match the JSON your `execute()`
expects, then update `Plugin::metadata()` so the host can present the
tool correctly to the LLM.
